This paper explores the nature of political discussions in online communication spaces, specifically on Reddit. It analyzes interaction and linguistic patterns within and between politically homogeneous and heterogeneous communication spaces. This paper involves natural language processing and social network analysis, which are common in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), social and information networks (cs.SI), and social computing (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical and practical implications of the findings, which could also fit under the sub-categories of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
